The article discusses the potential benefits and risks associated with the development of 5G networks. It highlights how 5G technology can revolutionize various industries and improve connectivity between devices. However, it also emphasizes the national security risks that come with this ultra-connected world. The article suggests that cyberattacks in a 5G world could have significant consequences, such as causing traffic jams on Election Day or manipulating assembly lines to harm companies. The Trump administration is committed to addressing these challenges by working with the private sector, civil society, and technology community. The article mentions an executive order signed by President Trump to secure the information and communications technology supply chain. The article concludes by emphasizing the importance of building secure networks to protect data and ensure the prosperity and peace of the country.